OL,3,CThe scientists on global warming's
OL,4,Cfront line in the Arctic circle
OL,6,FThis warming is at a rate far faster
OL,7,Fthan previous fluctuations long before
OL,8,Fthe industrial revolution.
OL,10,FI asked Celas what his response is to
OL,11,Fpeople who deny man-made emissions are
OL,12,Fimpacting our climate. "It's a
OL,13,Fcomplicated question," he said.
OL,15,F"Usually those people don't want to
OL,16,Fget facts. But here we are, everybody
OL,17,Fwho lives in Svalbard can see changes
OL,18,F... a couple of decades ago it was
OL,19,Fpossible to cross the fjord directly
OL,20,Fwith the snow mobile."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
