OL,3,CThe scientists on global warming's
OL,4,Cfront line in the Arctic circle
OL,6,F"The islands in front of us right now
OL,7,Fwas part of the glacier before. So all
OL,8,Fthese changes have happened," Celas
OL,9,Fcontinued.
OL,11,F"And it is fact. So if you see a
OL,12,Fpicture of before and a picture of
OL,13,Ftoday, it is different. And it's not
OL,14,Fnaturally different,"
OL,16,FOver the next few days we'll be
OL,17,Fheading out to take a closer look at
OL,18,Fthe glaciers retreating fast and
OL,19,Ffollowing different scientific teams
OL,20,Fas they race to monitor ice cores
OL,21,Fbefore they melt.
